<div class="insidecol ui-state-highlight left">
	<div id="statusesExplanation">
		<h3>
			<span class="left ui-icon ui-icon-info"></span>PBIs in a release
		</h3>
		<div id="submenuInfo" class="hidden">
			<p>As a Product Owner you can plan an implementation of chosen 
				PBIs in a given time period - release. This allows you to strictly 
				control a process of a project development.</p>
			<p>Note that each PBI can be planned as a part of multiple
				releases.</p>
			<p>Also, you can track a progress of a development which is presented on
				release burndown chart. This chart contains data about remaining
				story points of PBIs involved in a particular release and sprints in which they
				are planned for realization.</p>
		</div>
		<a href="#" id="submenuInfoToggle">Show details</a>
	</div>
</div>
